&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Rapid Response Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Merton Rapid Response Team. Central London Community Healthcare NHS Trust (CLCH)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced nurse to join a growing community rapid response team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of the Rapid Response Team is to prevent unnecessary hospital admissions. Patients are assessed within their own home within 2 hours of referral.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service runs from 08.00 - 20.00 mon-fri and 10.00 -18.00 at weekends and bank holidays. Successful post holders must be able to work 37.5 hours across 7 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is comprised of nurses, physiotherapists and occupational therapists; with access to GPs, pharmacists, case managers, social services, dietitians and other specialist nursing and therapy services, all co-located at Merton Civic Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should be experienced and have a sound knowledge of the community. You will need the ability and clinical skills to work autonomously but to also work alongside other members of the multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have undertaken professional development and have extended clinical skills including advanced physical assessment skills or willingness to undertake.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Possession of a UK driving licence and access to a vehicle for business purposes is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A commitment to personal and service development is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Julia Russell, Advanced Nurse Practitioner and Clinical Lead on 07899912813&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sue Brooker, Clinical Operations Manager Merton Unplanned Care on 07500983614&lt;/p&gt;
